{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Boolean","mdn_url":"/pl/docs/Glossary/Boolean","locale":"pl","native":"Polski","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p><span class=\"seoSummary\"><strong>Boolean </strong>jest typem danych, który może przyjmować jedynie dwie wartośći - <code>true</code>, lub <code>false</code>, czyli prawda i fałsz.</span>W JavaScripcie naprzykład używa się ich by zadecydować, które części kodu wykonać (<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/if...else\">instrukcje if</a>) lub powtórzyć (<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/for\">pętle typu for</a>)</p>\n\n<p>Pseudokod obrazujący koncept.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">/* JavaScript if statement */</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>boolean conditional<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n   <span class=\"token comment\">// ten kod się wykona jeśli warunek jest prawdziy</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>boolean conditional<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"warunek jest prawdziwy\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"warunek jest fałszywy\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* JavaScript for loop */</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>control variable<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> boolean conditional<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> counter<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// kod się wykonuje dopóki warunek jest prawdziwy</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Ten kod wykona się 4 razy - dla i = 0,1,2,3\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Nazwa pochodzi od angielskiego matematyka <a title=\"George Boole\" href=\"https://pl.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Boole\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">George Boole</a>, który był pionierem logiki matematycznej.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"learn_more","title":"Learn more","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"general_knowledge","title":"General knowledge","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a title=\"Boolean\" href=\"https://pl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boolean_data_type\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Boolean</a> on Wikipedia</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"technical_reference","title":"Technical reference","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li>The JavaScript global object: <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>Boolean</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Data_structures\">JavaScript data types and data structures</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Learn more","id":"learn_more"}],"summary":"Boolean jest typem danych, który może przyjmować jedynie dwie wartośći - true, lub false, czyli prawda i fałsz.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Boolean","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"Boolean","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Boolean","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Booléen","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Boolean","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"불린","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Booleano","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Boolean (Булев, Логический тип данных)","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Boolean","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"布林","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"pl/glossary/boolean","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/pl/glossary/boolean/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/pl/docs/Glossary","title":"Glossary"},{"uri":"/pl/docs/Glossary/Boolean","title":"Boolean"}],"pageTitle":"Boolean - Glossary | MDN","noIndexing":false}}